            "name": "default",
            "notes": "<p>Our photography tells the story of our people, our operations, our communities and our customers. We use three types of photography: Customers ‘Thames Moments’, our people ‘Here For You’ and our operations ‘Size & Scale’.</p><p>Images have a flexible width depending on the breakpoint. The height is depending on the aspect ratio of the uploaded image.</p><p>All images have a coded rounded corner as brand treatment depending on the position on the page.</p><p>To optimise the loading on images we are using the <code>&lt;picture&gt;</code> element, this allows us to define image sizes for each breakpoint, providing the user the best possible experience.</p><h5>Central Image Sizes</h5><p><strong>Extra Small:</strong> 640px (Screen size 320px and below)<br /><strong>Small:</strong> 1088px (Screen size 543px and below)<br /><strong>Medium:</strong> 938px (Screen size 767px and below)<br /><strong>Large:</strong> 1310px (Screen size 1023px and below)<br /><strong>Extra Large:</strong> 1804px (Screen size 1024px and above)</p>",
